<p>I am a privacy researcher, evaluator, and advocate graduating in May 2023 with my PhD in <a href="https://www.colorado.edu/cmci/infoscience">Information Science</a> from the <a href="https://www.colorado.edu">University of Colorado Boulder</a>. I study how young people understand privacy with <a href="https://www.ricarose.com/">Ricarose Roque</a> in the <a href="https://www.creativecommunities.group/">Creative Communities Research Group</a> and <a href="https://benshapi.ro/">Ben Shapiro</a> in the <a href="https://www.playfulcomputation.group/">Laboratory for Playful Computation</a>. Additionally, I produce quantitative and written analyses of privacy as an evaluator for <a href="https://www.commonsensemedia.org/">Common Sense Media</a>â€™s <a href="https://privacy.commonsense.org/">Privacy Program</a>. Previously, I earned my B.S. in Management Information Systems from the <a href="https://catalog.ua.edu/undergraduate/commerce-business-administration/information-systems-statistics-management-science/">Department of Information Systems, Statistics and Management Science</a> at the <a href="https://www.ua.edu/">University of Alabama</a> in 2018.</p>

